<HEADLINE> Dow Announces Study for Facility in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- World chemical giant Dow
Chemical Company announced today that it will study the
feasibility of building a world-scale production facility for
chloromethane products in China.
</P>
<P>
The study includes an assessment of various sites in China and
various technologies to produce the family of chloromethane
products to meet Asian demand, it said in a press release from its
headquarters in Michigan, U.S..
</P>
<P>
The chloromethane include methyl chloride, methylene chloride
and chloroform,, which are widely used by the chemical industry in
a variety of applications and are also used as solvents.
</P>
<P>
Dow is currently a major supplier of methylene chloride and
chloroform to China as well as other parts of Asia, having
world-scale production facilities in Germany and in Texas and
Louisiana of U.S., it said.
</P>
<P>
As the world's largest chloromethane producer, with capacity
above one billion pounds, Dow's global chlorinated organics
business is committed to satisfying the future needs of its
customers in China and the rest of the world, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Chemical Company is the fifth largest chemical company
in the world, with annual sales of more than $20 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
