<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU to Grant Uganda US$338,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
decided to grant Uganda 338,000 U.S. Dollars through Africa 2000,
a regional project of the United Nations Development Program
(UNDP), reported Radio Uganda today.
</P>
<P>
The money is to be utilised to support community grass root
projects aimed at fighting poverty in the country's five
districts.
</P>
<P>
The agreement for the grant will be signed by UNDP and
European Union here tomorrow afternoon.
</P>
<P>
African 2000 is a UNDP project which supports community
initiative aimed at protecting environment and promoting
ecologically sustainable development of economy.
</P>
<P>
The project provides financial and technical assistance to
grass root groups and non-governmental organisations involved in
natural resource regeneration and conservation.
</P>
<P>
An equal grant has been extended by EU to Africa 2000 for
countries of Burkina Faso and Cameroun in west Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
