<HEADLINE> Iran Strongly Slams Israel-US-Turkey War Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian government today
strongly slammed the Israel-US-Turkey joint military maneuvers
scheduled for mid-November.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi stated that such
cooperation is a source of crisis in the region and is against the
world of Islam.
</P>
<P>
"Iran considers Turkey a member of the Islamic community
but rejects its cooperation with the Zionist regime as it is
detrimental to the interests of the Muslims in the region," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman condemned the scheduled joint maneuver between
Turkey and Israel and called it a threat to Arab states as
well as the whole region.
</P>
<P>
"The Zionist regime through this joint maneuver intends to
weaken the Arab side in the equations of the region," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman stated "Iran has time and again voiced its
utmost concern over the increasing influences of the Zionist
regime in the region and cannot be indifferent toward these
developments."
</P>
<P>
Stating that Tehran considers coordinated policies amongst
Islamic countries as a major obstacle in the way of the
Israeli regime's expansionism, Mohammadi declared Iran's support
for any decisive stance against the expansionist policies of the
Zionist regime.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and Syria have already expressed their opposition to
the Israel-US-Turkey war games and rejected any justification that
the games were for rescue and search operations.
</P>
<P>
The military maneuvers involving troops of the three countries
will take place in mid-November in the eastern Mediterranean.
</P>
</TEXT>
