<HEADLINE> London Exchange Trades More Contracts in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The London International
Financial Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) traded 16.58
million contracts in August, an increase of 33 percent over the
same month of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Average daily volume amounted to 829,111 futures and options
contracts, representing a daily nominal turnover of 183 billion
pounds (about 300 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Statistics released today show that since the beginning of this
year, LIFFE's cumulative volume has totaled 135.94 million futures
and options contracts, a rise of 25 percent on the same period in
1996.
</P>
<P>
Deniel Hodson, LIFFE's Chief of Executive, said "The record
volume for the month of August reflects factors such as a rise in
Britain's interest rates and speculation over a possible rise in
German interest rates." 
</P>
</TEXT>
