<HEADLINE> Istanbul to Build Third Bridge linking Asia and </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish government
announced today that a third bridge linking Asia and Europe is to
be built in Istanbul, the country's largest city.
</P>
<P>
This decision was made at a meeting of the High Planning
Council held this morning, according to the semi-official Anatolia
 News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that the construction of a third bridge
aimed to cope with the increasingly growing traffic pressure.
</P>
<P>
The two bridges, the Bosphorus Bridge and the Fatih Sultan
Mehmet Bridge, across the Bosphorus Strait are not sufficient enough
to facilitate vehicles running between Asian and European sides.
</P>
<P>
The High Planning Council meeting, however, failed to announce
the concrete site where the third bridge will be built.
</P>
<P>
Instanbul's population has been increasing quickly due to
large numbers of migrants from underdeveloped eastern and
southeastern Turkey, bringing huge pressure on urban traffic.
</P>
</TEXT>
