<HEADLINE> Comoran Army Takes "Dispersuasive Action" against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Comoran army landed today
on the separatist island of Anjouan in a "dispersuasive action"
against the separatists who declared the island independent and
called for return of French rule on August 3.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Wadaane Mahamoud, the charge d'affaires of the Comoros in
Paris, said that the action is aimed at "making the separatists
under stand that one cannot return to the past."
</P>
<P>
He said that national unity and independence are "two
essential points on which the authorities cannot compromise."
</P>
<P>
He added that the Comoran troops have taken under their control
the strategic points of the island without a fight and that "the
situation is now normal."
</P>
<P>
The Comoran government announced this afternoon that the green
national flag of the Indian Ocean island nation was once again
flying on government buildings and mosques of Anjouan, replacing
the tricolor French flag which had flown there for one month,
according to Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
About 200 to 300 Comoran troops landed on the island at 02:00
GMT from two vessels taken from civilians, and took control of the
airport, the port of Mutsamudu and the town of Domoni by
afternoon, reported AFP.
</P>
<P>
The Comoran Foreign Ministry said today that "authority of the
state" was reestablished "without the flow of blood."
</P>
</TEXT>
