<HEADLINE> Security Council to Hold Ministerial Meeting on Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council of
the United Nations decided today to hold a ministerial-level
meeting on Africa on September 25, council president Bill
Richardson of the United States said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after council consultations, Richardson
said the objective of the meeting would be to make a positive
statement on Africa.
</P>
<P>
"We want to focus on conflict-resolution, on development.... We
hope to circulate a draft very soon on this issue in the days
ahead," he said.
</P>
<P>
African issues that the Security Council has been concerned
about in these months are the situation in Somalia, Sierra Leone,
Burundi, Rwanda, the Republic of the Congo, the Democratic
Republic of the Congo and the territory of Western Sahara. 
