<HEADLINE> Improvement of Urban Living Environnment Urged in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Minister of State in
the Prime Minister's Office, Mussa Nkhangaa, today called for an
improvement of the living environment in urban areas of Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Nkhangaa made the appeal while opening a three-day consultative
meeting on City Health Plan for Dar es Salaam Health City Project.
</P>
<P>
He noted that whereas urban population is increasing at an alarming
rate, town planning does not conform to the reality of the city and
urban.
</P>
<P>
He said that urban dwellers in the country are in danger of
contracting various diseases if appropriate measures are not initiated
to improve the surrounding environment.
</P>
<P>
Most of the urban dwellers live in poor quality housing with
congested rooms, inadequate provision of clean and safe water, and
poor sewerage systems, but with no waste disposal systems in place,
Nkhangaa said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, jointly organized by the Dar es Salaam City
Commission, the World Health Organization (WHO), the Tanzanian
Ministry of Health, among other things, reviews the current health
situation in the city and the problems encountered in the provision
of health care. 
</P>
