<HEADLINE> Tanzanian PM for Affordable Insurance Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Prime
Minister Frederick Sumaye today urged insurance practitioners to
devise ways of making the insurance business sustainable, of high
quality and affordable by majority of the people in the country.
</P>
<P>
When launching the Tanzania Insurance Day in the capital,
Sumaye said that insurance agents and other practitioners should
utilize the existing good insurance policy and legal frame work
to attract customers by making it of good quality but affordable.
</P>
<P>
In order to get high value insurance products but of lower
premiums, the establishment of minimal standards in the conduct
of the insurance business is necessary, according to the prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
He challenged the practitioners to expand insurance coverage
to rural areas and middle income earners, saying the large scale
livestock keepers, crop producers, fishermen, construction
workers and other groups should be covered by the insurance
services.
</P>
<P>
Sumaye also expressed the need for promotion of regional
cooperation in the insurance industry within East Africa and
later to other parts of the region. 
