<HEADLINE> Dow Has Marginal Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks failed to go
higher today despite their big volume, closing with only marginal
gains compared to Tuesday's powerful rally.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average, which jumped 257 points
Tuesday, rose just 14.86 to 7,894.64, down from an earlier
65-point gain.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a 3-to-2 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 548.69 million shares,
more than the 491.83 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 0.27 to 927.85, the
NYSE composite index rose 0.81 to 483.71, and the Nasdaq composite
index rose 0.15 to 1,618.24.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 rose 0.74 to 428.79, its eighth consecutive
winning session; and the small-company dominated American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 3.13 to 660.00 for its second
straight closing high.
</P>
<P>
Stocks were rising steadily during the afternoon until interest
rates rose in the bond market after the release of some robust
auto sales data. 
</P>
</TEXT>
