<HEADLINE> Tung Confident Hong Kong, S'pore of Scaling New Heights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chief Executive of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa
said here today that he was confident that both Hong Kong and
Singapore will scale new heights of achievements in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a welcome dinner given by Singapore Prime Minister
Goh Chok Tong, Tung said: "July 1, 1997 was a date to which we in
Hong Kong have looked forward to with pride and confidence."
</P>
<P>
"Pride that we at last will be united with China and to become
masters of our own destiny. Confidence that we can and will make
our city a even better place for our children and grandchildren,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong to China can not be more timely. Never
did China as a nation have such prosperity as she has today, nor
has China achieved greater recognition and dignity in the
international community as she has today," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"We in Hong Kong look forward to a 21st century China which is
even more stable, open, and prosperous and a China which has taken
a rightful place among leaders of community of nations of the
world," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
"I firmly believe that a prosperous and successful Hong Kong
working under the One Country, Two System Concept in the years to
come can contribute greatly to China as she moves forward
confidently into the 21st century. We in Hong Kong, in turn, can
benefit greatly from a successful and confident China. So too I
believe can Singapore and the rest of this region," he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Tung arrived here this afternoon on a three-day visit, his
first to Singapore as the Chief Executive of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
He said that he has come to Singapore to see for himself what
Singapore has achieved and that he is particularly interested in
the fields of education and housing which are key concerns for his
administration.
</P>
<P>
"Both Hong Kong and Singapore have achieved a great deal over
the past 50 years. But together, we can work harder. We can do
better. We are competitors sometimes, but other times we are very
complimentary. And it is important we continue to work together. I
am confident that both of us will scale new heights of
achievements in the 21st century," Tung said.
</P>
</TEXT>
