<HEADLINE> Palestinian Representative Condemn Jerusalem Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian
representative in the United States on Thursday condemned a bomb
attack in Jerusalem, which killed five people and injured more
than 100.
</P>
<P>
"We condemn in the strongest terms these terrorist acts,
which we believe are intended to sabotage the peace process and
undermine the efforts of the U.S.Secretary of State (Madeleine
Albright)," Hassan Abdel Rahman, the representative, told CNN
shortly after the bombings occurred at a downtown Jerusalem
pedestrian mall packed with shoppers and tourists.
</P>
<P>
Albright was scheduled to leave for the Middle East on
September 9, in an attempt to revive the peace process
that has been suspended since last March when the Israeli
government decided to build a Jewish neighborhood in Arab East
jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
"We hope ... she will proceed on her trip," Abdel Rahman
said.
</P>
<P>
U.S. State Department officials said no decision had been
made on whether to postpone Albright's trip to Israel and other
Middle East countries. 
