<HEADLINE> U.N. Declares Mozambique Island World Heritage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Education, Scientific and Culture Organisation (UNESCO) has
declared Mozambique Island a world heritage.
</P>
<P>
UNESCO director general Frederico Mayor made the offer today
in the Mozambican capital, Maputo, according to a report reaching
here.
</P>
<P>
UNESCO has also given the Mozambican government 11 million
U.S. dollars to preserve the island.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique Island is located three kilometres off the coast of
the northern province of Nampula. It was the first Portuguese
colonial capital.
</P>
<P>
Besides rehabilitating historical monuments, work to restore
Mozambique Island also aims to improve the living conditions of
about 7000 people who live on it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
