<HEADLINE> Education in Students' Overall Development Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing,
speaking at a symposium on primary and middle-school education
today, said that every effort should be made to develop primary
and middle-school education.
</P>
<P>
It should cater to all children, he said, and there should be
less selecting of superior students and more universal secondary
education.
</P>
<P>
He said that primary and middle schools with lower educational
levels should be helped in order to narrow gaps in education, and
that they should develop students overall, including ethically,
intellectually and physically. They should focus on easing
students' burden in studies with better curricula, textbooks, and
teaching methods.
</P>
<P>
More scientific entrance exams and assessment procedures should
be used to provide a positive role in education, he said.
</P>
<P>
The quality of primary and middle-school teachers should be
improved and the education structure adjusted to create favorable
conditions for education, he said.
</P>
<P>
This needs the support of governments at various levels and of
society, which should in turn increase funding and provide
favorable policies for education, Li concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
