<HEADLINE> Better Use of Mineral Resources Called for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua said
today that the sound development of China's mining industry needs
a better use of mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came in a speech today at the fifth meeting of the
National Mineral Resources Committee, which Zou heads.
</P>
<P>
Zou emphasized the need of the present and future generations
to develop mineral resources, and that "Illicit mining must
be banned, and foreign resources should be used."
</P>
<P>
He said that use of mineral resources must ensure that
resources remain state property, there are prospecting and
exploitation licenses issued by proper departments, and that
mining companies pay for mineral rights.
</P>
<P>
This year, the National Mineral Resources Committee has
overseen the revision of regulations related to the Mineral
Resources Law, continued research on development of mineral
resources overseas, set up a petroleum and gas office, made
proposals on reforming the state-owned mining industry, and
prepared for a forum on economic development in central China.
</P>
