<HEADLINE> Lebanese Communist Party Leader Praises China's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Communist Party
leader Faruk Dahrouj today highly praised the progress China has
made since the 14th National People's Congress (NPC) of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) in 1992.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua News Agency reporter here today,
the leader said that over the past five years, Chinese economy
has witnessed a fast, stable and sustained growth and the
people's living standards have been improved.
</P>
<P>
"All the achievements should be attributed to the correct
leadership of the CPC and its reform and opening-up policy," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming 15th National People's Congress, which is to
convene on September 12, is an important meeting for China as it
will further perfect China's policy in its drive to lead Chinese
people into a new century, the leader noted.
</P>
<P>
China began to implement a reform and opening-up policy in
1980 with economic development as the top priority. This led
China achieve an average annual growth rate of 8 percent, making
it one of the countries in the world with fastest growing economy.
</P>
<P>
On Hong Kong and Taiwan issue, the Lebanese leader said that
Hong Kong has returned to China on July 1. This proved the
feasibility and correctness of the "one country, to systems"
policy created by late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan is part of China and can not be separated from it. The
unity of mainland and Taiwan will come true in the near future,
the Lebanese communist party leader said. 
