<HEADLINE> U.S. Congress Honors Diana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September (Xinhua) -- The United States Congress
has decided to proclaim a "National Day of Recognition" on
Saturday when Princess Diane is buried.
</P>
<P>
The Senate approved Wednesday a resolution lauding Diana for
her good deeds, which included promoting AIDS awareness, working
for a worldwide ban on land mines and supporting various
children's causes.
</P>
<P>
It proclaimed Saturday, the day of her funeral in London, to be
a National Day of Recognition for her deeds.
</P>
<P>
House Speaker Newt Gingrich said the House would vote to honor
Diana with a similar measure.
</P>
<P>
Diana was killed at the age of 36 early Sunday in a car crash
in Paris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
