<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Universities Sign Agreement With Network Supplier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Three major tertiary
institutions, Hong Kong Baptist University, the Hong Kong
Institute of Education and the Hong Kong Polytechnic University,
signed a agreement today with Novell, a leading supplier of
network software.
</P>
<P>
Under the Master License Agreement (MLA), the universities will
upgrade their operating system to IntranetWare and implement other
network management services such as Novell Application Launcher
and Novell Replication Services.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Baptist University found that with Novell, it is able
to offer "broader and more cost-effective" network-based services
to its students and staff.
</P>
<P>
"Our university demanded a resilient network backbone and an
integrated network management facility," said Jerome J. Day,
director of Computing and Telecommunications Services Center at
Hong Kong Baptist University.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Institute of Education, which focuses on teacher
education, and the Hong Kong Polytechnic University also said
Novell provides them with fairly comprehensive network solutions.
</P>
<P>
According to Michael Wan, managing director of Novell Hong Kong
Ltd., the universities' ability to provide leading information
technology solutions to its students and staff is crucial to
providing top-notch educational services, which, in turn, are
essential in developing talents to support Hong Kong's continued
growth and competitive edge.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
