<HEADLINE> SAR Government Expresses Condolences Over Air-Crash Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) government today expressed condolences
to the families of four Hong Kong residents killed in a plane
crash in Cambodia on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We have been maintaining close liaison with the Office of the
Commissioner of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the People's
Republic of China in Hong Kong over this incident," a government
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese Embassy in Phnom Penh will render
appropriate assistance to the families of the victims who are Hong
Kong residents.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Immigration Department has been in
contact with the Consulate General of Cambodia and with the
airline concerned in order to contact the families of the victims
to see if any practical assistance is required.
</P>
<P>
A twin-engine Tupolev 134 of Vietnam Airlines crashed in
torrential rain at Phnom Penh's Pochentong international airport
Wednesday, killing more than 60 people aboard.  
