<HEADLINE> Iraqi Newspaper Calls For Arab Unity Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi newspaper "Al-Thawara"
today called on the Arabs to get united against the
Israeli-U.S.-Turkish alliance.
</P>
<P>
Since the late 1970s, Turkey has been playing a dangerous
game which is part of a long-term U.S.-Israeli plan designed to
put pressure on nations of the region by keeping them under
constant threat of aggression, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The paper added that this plan serves no one but the U.S. and
Israel and Turkey is the loser in all cases.
</P>
<P>
"Al-Thawara" described the joint Turkish-U.S.-Israeli military
exercises, scheduled in November in the Mediterranean, as a
fresh piece of evidence that the relationship between Turkey and
Israel is a strategic political and military alliance with its
head in Washington and its arms in Ankara and Tel-Aviv.
</P>
<P>
The paper pointed out that Israel is seeking to make Turkey to
be the second jaw of a pair of pincers to close in upon the region
by threatening or sponsoring aggression on it.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. is now more eager than ever to establish a military
alliance in southwest Asia with the aim of minimizing the European
Union's role in the region and strengthening Israel militarily so
as to ensure its strategic superiority over the Arabs, said the
paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
