<HEADLINE> Jordanian-Syrian Trade Exceeds 130 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Trade volume between Jordan
and Syria exceeded 130 million U.S. dollars in 1996, a Jordanian
official disclosed here today.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Mustafa Khreisat, director of Jordan's
pavilion at the current Damascus International Exhibition in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
Still, there is a wide prospect for expanding trade between the
two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Khreisat said trade balance in 1996 was in favor of Syria, when
Jordan imported some 90 million dollars worth of goods whereas
exports valued at about 40 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's most important imports from Syria are ready-made
clothes while cement tops Jordan's exports to Syria, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen Jordanian industrial companies are participating in the
current Damascus International Exhibition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
