<HEADLINE> China to Issue Second 1997 Account Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- China will issue this year's
second batch of account bonds on Friday, the Ministry of Finance
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year account bonds are valued at 13 billion yuan and
will be registered and can be traded on the Shanghai and Shenzhen
stock markets immediately after the issue closes on September 24.
</P>
<P>
They will carry an annual interest of 9.78 percent. The leading
underwriter is the China Investment Bank, with the Everbright Bank
of China and the Shanghai Urban Cooperative Bank as the deputy
underwriters.
</P>
<P>
The bonds will be offered through the Shanghai and Shenzhen
securities exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Investors can buy the bonds through their securities accounts
on the two securities exchanges, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
China issued more than 195 billion yuan in treasury bonds last
year.  
</P>
