<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 13:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Reimposes Total Closure on Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 4 (Xinhua)-- Israel reimposed today a
total closure of the Palestinian self-rule territories after three
suspected suicide bombings in central Jerusalem killed at least
five people and wounded 140 others.
</P>
<P>
The closure order was given by Israeli Defense Minister
Yitzhak Mordechai after he learned about the bombings, which were
claimed by the anti-Israeli Palestinian organization, the Islamic
Resistance Movement (Hamas).
</P>
<P>
At least three consecutive bomb explosions went off in the
crowded Ben Yehuda Street pedestrian mall at about 15:00 local
time (noon GMT).
</P>
<P>
Israeli television showed pictures of the explosion scene in
the pedestrian mall in central Jerusalem, which was in chaos. A
large number of ambulances arrived at the site and police and
rescue workers rushed to evacuated the wounded, many of whose
bodies covered with blood, to hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem police said that among the three dead, at least two
of them were suspected to be Hamas suicide bombers. Eyewitnesses
said they saw body parts clad with clothing scattered on the
street, indicating the grave magnitude of the explosions.
</P>
<P>
Police have sealed off the area.
</P>
<P>
There were conflicting reports over the number of explosions,
but it was believed that there occurred three explosions in
seconds apart.
</P>
<P>
This was the second terror attack since the July 30 twin
suicide bombings in Jerusalem's Mahane Yehuda market, about one
kilometer away from today's bombing site, killing 17 people and
wounding 170 others. As usual, the Israeli government is expected
to react strongly.
</P>
<P>
Israel radio reported that Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
has canceled all his scheduled activities in order to deal with
the situation.
</P>
<P>
The terror attack took place just one week before the first
visit by United States Secretary of State Medeleine Albright to
the region aimed at reviving the peace process with Israelis and
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Hamas has claimed responsibility for the July 30 twin suicide
bombings in Jerusalem Mahane Yehuda market that killed 17 people
and wounded 170 others.
</P>
<P>
Israel has just eased the total blockade on the Palestinian
self-rule territories early the week, which was imposed after the
July 30 bombings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
