<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Soar on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
move higher on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index increased by 6.43 points to close at 1826.61
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 282.83 million units, valued
at 623 million Singapore dollars (about 409.87 million U.S.
dollars). Declines continued to overwhelm advances by 286 to 99
while 219 other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Ber Group was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 12.87 million units. It was followed by Magnum
Corporation which had 11.71 million shares traded. Public Banking
Foreign was next with 11.57 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 2.2 dollars to finish at 23 Singapore
dollars. Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 increased by
1.6 dollars to end at 31.8 Singapore dollars. The Singapore
Airlines Foreign gained 90 cents to close at 11.9 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, MAA was the biggest loser as it declined by
5.2 dollars to end at 3.1 Singapore dollars. ASEAN Fund fell by
4.3 dollars to close at 10.7 U.S. dollars while Hong Leong Credit
finished 2.6 dollars lower at 2.8 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
