<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Exports More Textiles, Apparel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's textile and
apparel exports reached 1.78 billion U.S. dollars in the first
five months of this year and accounted for 45 percent of the
country's total industrial exports, according to the Export Broad.
</P>
<P>
During the period, textile and apparel exports recorded an
increase of 11 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Since 1986, textiles and apparel have been Sri Lanka's main
export items. But at the same time, the country has been
importing, mainly from Asia, more than 90 percent of fabrics
needed by the export garment sector.
</P>
<P>
Since Sri Lanka does not grow cotton and produces little
man-made fiber, foreign businessmen are encouraged to invest in
the sectors to produce the raw materials, the board said.
</P>
</TEXT>
