<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maintains Political, Social Stability (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chen said the broad masses of the people have developed a keen
awareness and a greater ability to withstand various social risks as
the country's reform and opening drive continue to expand.
</P>
<P>
Some 10 million workers across the country have been declared
redundant, with a large number of people finding reemployment with
the help of governments at various levels and society. Chinese
people trust the government, and are willing to tide over
difficulties and share risk.
</P>
<P>
"This represents one of the most active and essential changes
in China's political and social life. This is, in fact, the basis
for confidence that China can overcome difficulties and make new
progress," said Chen.
</P>
<P>
He attributed these changes to the role of the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core in the nation's political
life.
</P>
<P>
The role of China's leadership finds expression primarily in
making policy decisions on major issues. The CPC always solicits
opinions of the CPPCC, various non-Communist parties, mass
organizations and representatives from various segments of the
community. The fact that said groups offer suggestions on major
issues and decisions has a profound impact on both the national
economy and the livelihood of the people.
</P>
<P>
Decisions are eventually implemented by the government after
being examined and endorsed by the NPC, said Chen, adding that the
said political system currently operates in line with actual life
in China.
</P>
<P>
He said the role of core leadership of the CPC over China's
political life is also reflected in the pioneering and exemplary
role of 58 million members of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Practice has proved that China's current political system is
effective, said Chen.
</P>
<P>
"China will continue its efforts to introduce a socialist
market economic structure and to reform its political structure,
carry forward positive achievements and avoid mistakes in order to
score even greater achievements in democracy and a legal system,"
said Chen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970904.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maintains Political, Social Stability (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- China's political and social
life has remained relaxed and stable from grass roots through the
highest level for a number of years, according to a senior
official from the National Committee Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Chen Jinyu, deputy secretary-general of CPPCC, noted that China
has scored tremendous achievements in reform and opening up over
the past five years, with notable successes in democracy and the
introduction of a legal system, as well as economic development.
</P>
<P>
"Encouraging changes have taken place in the country's
political and social life in the wake of numerous achievements,"
according to Chen.
</P>
<P>
Common people in grass roots units, including factory workers,
farmers, intellectuals, traders and laborers, "are living a
relaxed life", with a constantly expanding range of employment,
self-development channels and choices, said Chen.
</P>
<P>
"People now can achieve prosperity through labor, and their
legitimate incomes are protected by law," according to the deputy
secretary-general. "Intellectuals can give a full play to their
intelligence and wisdom, and realize their ambitions, with society
providing much more opportunities than in the past."
</P>
<P>
The fact that ordinary Chinese people have been living a more
relaxed life and the democratic atmosphere has permeated social
life, coupled with a sense of security, serves as important
indicators for China's political stability and a necessary
condition for social progress, said Chen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970904.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maintains Political, Social Stability (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chen pointed to the upper echelon of leadership by noting that
the nation's political life has remained normal and stable. The
country, under the leadership by the CPC Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core, has retained conventional approaches for
implementing predetermined plans for all sectors since the death
of Deng Xiaoping in February.
</P>
<P>
The annual sessions of the National People's Congress (NPC) and
the CPPCC National Committee were successfully held, and Hong
Kong's smooth return to the motherland represented a great step
towards peacefully reunifying the motherland. The 15th CPC
national congress will be convened as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
Predictions that "China would surely witness chaos following
the death of Deng Xiaoping" have proved to be completedly wrong,
said Chen.
</P>
<P>
CPC Central Committee General Secretary Jiang Zemin's speech
delivered at the Party School of the CPC Central Committee on May
29 this year showed that the CPC's third generation of leadership
with Jiang at the core will continue to hold high the banner of
Deng's theory on building socialism with Chinese characteristics,
according to Chen.
</P>
<P>
"China's reform and opening policies have not changed, but
instead have been carried out in a more pragmatic manner. This
demonstrates that China's policies will not change simply because
of the change of leaders, and that the political life of the
country's upper echelon of leaders remained systematic," said
Chen.
</P>
</TEXT>
