<HEADLINE> 3 Explosions Go off in Jerusalem, 3 Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 4 (Xinhua) -- At least three people were
killed in three consecutive bomb explosions in down town Jerusalem
this afternoon with many casualties and extensive damages.
</P>
<P>
At least 26 people were wounded when the explosions went off in
the crowded Ben Yehuda Street pedestrian mall at about 15:00 local
time (noon GMT), according to the military radio.
</P>
<P>
A number of people lying on the ground after the explosions,
according to one radio report.
</P>
<P>
Ambulances rushed to the scene and the wounded are seen taken
away, Israeli tv showed.
</P>
<P>
Police have sealed off the area.
</P>
<P>
Police were quoted in radio as believing that the explosions
were set off by a suicide bomber.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place just one week before the first
visit by the United States Secretary of State Medeleine Albright
to the region aimed at brokering peace between Israelis and
Palestinians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
