<HEADLINE> At Least 4 Killed in Explosions in Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 4 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were
killed and 100 others wounded in three consecutive bomb explosions
in down town Jerusalem this afternoon with many casualties and
extensive damages.
</P>
<P>
The explosions went off in the crowded Ben Yehuda Street
pedestrian mall at about 15:00 local time (noon GMT).
</P>
<P>
Ambulances rushed to the scene and the wounded are seen taken
away, Israeli tv showed.
</P>
<P>
Police have sealed off the area.
</P>
<P>
Police were quoted by radio stations as believing that the
explosions were set off by a suicide bomber of the anti-Israeli
militant group, the Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas).
</P>
<P>
Israel radio reported that Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
has cancelled all his scheduled activities in order to deal with
the situation.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place just one week before the first
visit by the United States Secretary of State Medeleine Albright
to the region aimed at brokering peace between Israelis and
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Hamas has claimed responsibility for the July 30 twin suicide
bombings in Jerusalems Mahane Yehuda market that killed 17 people
and wounded 170 others. 
