<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Slip Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Australian shares closed
marginally lower today with a poor performance by some leading
resource stocks weighing heavily on the market.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 10.5 points down at 2,608.5.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 334.68 million shares with a trading
value of 807.8 million Australian dollars (589.6 million US
dollars). Falling stocks shaded rising stocks, 527 to 515.
</P>
<P>
Leading mining stocks all tumbled, with market bellwether BHP
down 27.8 cents to 16.73 Australian dollars, Rio Tinto falling 28
to 19.87 Australian dollars, WMC easing 11 to 6.94 Australian
dollars and Pasminco dropping seven to 2.42 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Gold eased 40 US cents in 322.10 US dollars in late trade on
the Sydney exchange, but the related index slipped marginally by
0.2 points to 1,311.8.
</P>
<P>
Other resource stocks results were mixed, as the All Resources
index fell 10.3 points to 1,354.4. Oil and gas company Woodside
gained 25 cents to 11.55 Australian dollars after its record
interim profit of 152 million Australian dollars (110 million US
dollars) yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said banking stocks offered little direction as the
index dropped 15.0 points to 4,883.3. National Australia Bank
slipped two to 19.05 Australian dollars, ANZ lost 23 to 9.74
Australian dollars, Westpac was steady at 7.83 Australian dollars
and Commonwealth gained 10 to close at 15.34 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Trade in industrial stocks was quieter with the index dropping
11.8 points to 4,213.9 at the close.  
</P>
</TEXT>
