<HEADLINE> CIC to Run Netscape's Internet Site in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- China Internet Corporation
(CIC) today announced that it has signed a strategic agreement
with Netscape Communications Corporation, under which CIC will
become Netscape's international Internet site affiliate in China.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said that CIC will be responsible for
launching and running Netscape's Internet site in China, as well
as for localizing information and developing local content.
</P>
<P>
CIC will deliver worldwide financial news and services to
individuals and business professionals, and it will also help
bring Netscape's Netcenter -- a new free online service announced
today -- to corporations in China.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yunsheng, chairman and CEO of CIC, said: "This affiliate
agreement represents a major step in the development of online
information and services in China and will play a significant role
in the growth of the Internet and online services in China."
</P>
<P>
CIC has been responsible for the creation of China Wide Web
(CWW), the core of a nationwide online business information
infrastructure project that spans the whole country.
</P>
<P>
The company has set up a key strategic partnership with China's
Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications, as a result of which the
CWW service is available to Chinese Internet subscribers in more
than 200 cities across China.  
</P>
