<DOCNO> XIE19970904.0142 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investments Soar in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Investments approved by the
Board of Investments of the Philippines surged by 427 percent to
476.6 billion pesos (16 billion U.S. dollars) during the first
eight months of this year from last year's 90.42 billion pesos (3
billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Equity investments rose by 396 percent from 31.03 billion pesos
(1 billion dollars) in 1996 to 153.95 billion (5 billion dollars)
in 1997, with 68.8 percent coming from local investors, the board
said in a report today.
</P>
<P>
The remaining equity investments were made by foreign investors
such as France, Britain, the United States, Virgin Islands, Japan,
the Netherlands and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
In the month of August alone, the board approved 184.74 billion
pesos (6.2 billion dollars) worth of investments, almost 30 times
the 6.14 billion pesos (205 million dollars) registered in the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Investments by local businessmen still primarily boosted the
equity investments during the month, which rose to 46.6 billion
pesos (1.6 billion dollars) from 1.95 billion pesos (65 million
dollars) in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
