<HEADLINE> Ramos Orders Probe of Explosion in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos today ordered police to conduct an immediate investigation
into an explosion that took place last night in Manila.
</P>
<P>
In a directive to Interior and Local Government Secretary
Robert Barbers and National Police Director General Recaredo
Sarimento, Ramos asked them to report back to him as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed and 49 others injured in the explosion
in front of a shop.  
