<HEADLINE> Iran to Launch Massive Military Maneuvers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Iran is to launch three land,
air and sea war games on the occasion of the Defense Week from
September 22 to 28.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA quoted Mehdi Chamran, cultural
deputy of the Armed Forces Headquarters, as saying that the
exercises are aimed at displaying the defense potentials and
combat power.
</P>
<P>
He said that "Zulfaqar" maneuvers will be carried out by the
ground forces, "Ra'd" by the Air Forces and the "Pirouzi-8"
jointly by the Navy and the Islamic Revolution's Guards Corps.
</P>
<P>
The report said the war games will mark the 17th anniversary of
the 1980-88 war between Iran and Iraq.
</P>
<P>
However, the report gave no details about the military
maneuvers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
