<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Implements Forest Management Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank-aided forest
resources management project (FRMP) in Bangladesh has made good
progress, sources from the World Bank said here today.
</P>
<P>
More than 31,000 hectares of new mangroves and industrial
plantations have been already established under the FRMP, the
sources added.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Bangladesh's forest departments have done a good job
in the preparation of integrated forest management plans,
environmental management, nature conservation and other areas.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank, one of the major donors to the project, has
expressed its satisfaction with the overall status of the project
implementation, the sources noted.
</P>
<P>
According to the World Bank sources, 53 percent of the
36.3-million-U.S.-dollar project has been completed.
</P>
<P>
The project includes forest resources management and expansion,
mainly through community participation. Pilot plantations for
community participation are expected to be established in the next
fiscal year starting July 1, 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
