<HEADLINE> Multimedia Atlas For Hong Kong SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A multimedia atlas on the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) has been published,
and will soon be available on the market, according to the State
Bureau of Surveying and Mapping.
</P>
<P>
The atlas, published by the China Map Publishing House, was
complied on the basis of the official atlas of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region issued by the State Council on July
1.
</P>
<P>
The atlas features more than 1,800 maps, photographs and
illustrations. The one million-character publication is divided
into eight sections covering various sectors of Hong Kong,
including history, geography, politics, the economy, transport,
tourism, shopping, entertainment, finance, trade, education and
culture.
</P>
<P>
The information is available on a CD-ROM. Readers can
use computers to scan videos and photos, in addition to listening
to music, conducting searches and printing desired information.
</P>
</TEXT>
