<HEADLINE> US Urged To Abide by Sino-US Joint Communiques on Taiwan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- China has expressed the hope
that the United States will strictly observe the spirit and
principles embodied in the three Sino-US joint communiques on
Taiwan issue and not allow Lee Teng-hui to use any opportunity
to conduct activities aimed at creating "two Chinas" or "one
China, one Taiwan".
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang made the remark
this afternoon during a routine press conference when asked about
Lee's transit visa issued by the US.
</P>
<P>
China has made repeated representations to the US on the issue,
said Shen, adding that some Taiwan leaders may use various
opportunities and occasions to conduct activities aimed at
creating "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan". He stressed that
such activities harm the relaxation of relations across the Taiwan
Straits and the process of the peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Shen also touched on the question of why some people in Taiwan
want to restore talks on relations across the Taiwan Straits,
while laying aside disputes over sovereignty. He noted that the
"one China" principle has the key importance in the relations
across the Taiwan Straits and there is no room for compromise over
the principle because Taiwan is part of China, and the government
of the People's Republic of China is the sole legitimate
government representing the whole of China, a fact duly recorded
in United Nations resolutions and accepted by the vast majority of
countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
Shen pointed out that there is absolutely no question
regarding laying aside disputes on the issue of China's
sovereignty and territorial integrity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970904.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Year 2000 Problem Hits Computers: Australian Expert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A computer expert with
Australia's largest company BHP claimed today that the "year 2000
problem" is already impacting on the performance of the world's
computer systems.
</P>
<P>
Michael Yastreboff, manager of the year 2000 problem for
resources giant BHP, told the Australian Unix and Open Systems
User Group Annual Conference that the problem has already started
to manifest itself in some areas.
</P>
<P>
BHP, or Broken Hill Proprietary Ltd. specializes in mining and
metalworking.
</P>
<P>
The areas to be affected include some automatic teller machines
(ATM) refusing to accept bank cards with an expiry year of 00,
which computers usually regard as the date missing, Yastreboff
said.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by the Australian Associated Press as warning
that the problem could affect up to 95 percent of all computer
applications in areas such as finance.
</P>
<P>
Some computers used for issuing driver's licenses have refused
to recognize any dates in the new millennium, although that
problem has since been fixed, he said.
</P>
<P>
Some thermostat manufacturers have admitted that their products
will fail in 2000.
</P>
<P>
"The reality is some of the newest thermostats actually
compensate for the fact that it's winter or summer," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Some prisoners (in the United States) were actually released
because in a computer their release year was 00, and the computer
interpreted that as 1900 and said 'those poor prisoners, they've
been in prison for that long'," he added.
</P>
<P>
"It actually printed some release orders, the prisoners got out
not knowing why, but I guess they're the only people who will
actually thank the year 2000 problem for something," he said.
</P>
<P>
In a similar incident which points to the problems that could
arise in 2000, two aluminum smelters, one in New Zealand and one
in Tasmania, an island off continental Australia, shut themselves
down at midnight on December 31, 1996, because they could not
calculate the end of the leap year.
</P>
<P>
Yastreboff said that around the home, equipment such as video
recorders and security systems are also liable to fail when year
2000 arrives.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970904.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
