<HEADLINE> China Strives To Improve Urban Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- China is to energetically push
forward urban environmental protection in a bid to improve the
urban ecology and people's quality of life, said Wang Yangzu,
deputy-director of the National Environmental Protection Agency.
</P>
<P>
Wang recently told Xinhua that China has made some progress in
controlling urban industrial pollution, greening cities and
improving urban ecology since east China's Zhangjiagang was
conferred the title of "Model City in Environmental Protection"
last year.
</P>
<P>
In general, however, the country still has a lot to do in urban
pollution control, Wang noted, adding that urban green belt
coverage rate is quite low and the environmental management still
needs improvement.
</P>
<P>
Wang stressed that China has to increase efforts to transform
all the cities into places with sustainable development, rapid and
healthy economic growth, a good environment and ecology, and
healthy residents.
</P>
<P>
As one of the steps toward the goal, China is to include the
yearly selection of the model environmentally-sound city into the
country's long-term social and economic development plan.
</P>
<P>
The title of "Model City in Environmental Protection" is the
country's highest honor in the field. The cities which receive the
recognition must have an overall clean environment while
witnessing rapid social and economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Many cities including Xiamen, Dalian and Zhuhai have been
striving for the honor, with the overall urban environment and
residents' lives improved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
