<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Justice Minister Elisabeth Guigou Wednesday presented to the
council of ministers her draft law on the prevention of sexual
infractions and the protection of the minors. This law, which
follows the outline of the one drafted by her predecessor Jacques
Toubon, installs a clause on socio-judicial supervision of those
who have committed sexual infractions and have been released from
jail, as well as a requirement for them to undergo medical and
psychological treatment.
</P>
