Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The resignation of the president of Air France, Christian
Blanc, has become inevitable as the road for compromise has become
totally blocked between him and the prime minister's office, which
has accused him of trying to exert pressure on the government by
threatening to resign and placing his allies, particularly the
powerful Force Ouvriere union, to the center of the enterprise
committee.
</P>
<P>
Blanc had been trying to persuade Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
to let Air France open part of its stocks to the market out of
economic and commercial considerations. This demand was strongly
opposed by Minister of Transport Jean-Claude Gayssot who is backed
by the Communist Party of France.
</P>
<P>
-- The Casino supermarket chain group announced Wednesday that
it will purchase 416 supermarkets of the Franprix chain group and
241 shops of the Leader Price hard discount chain group from the
American group TLC at a value of 2.8 billion francs (466 million
U.S. dollars). This double acquisition will consolidate the
position of Casino in France and give it the second place among
chain groups in the country, after Carrefour. 
