<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flourishing Ethnic Unity in China  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A group of resource development and infrastructure construction
projects have been launched in the autonomous regions, with the
increasing rate of the investment in both infrastructure
construction and technological renovations during the first half
of 1996 surpassing the rate for eastern areas for the first time
in history.
</P>
<P>
The central government increased its financial support to
ethnic minority regions in central and western China in 1996. In
May, it decided to allocate more than two billion yuan (230
million US dollars) in subsidies to ethnic minority regions. And
increased financial support by the central government has eased
the financial difficulties of these regions to some extent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chinese leaders, including President Jiang Zemin and
Premier Li Peng, have frequently visited Guizhou and Sichuan
provinces and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
A series of projects have been launched to provide ethnic
regions with improved living conditions, science and technology,
education, information, and modern culture.
</P>
<P>
The compulsory education project introduced in China's less
developed regions in 1996 is the largest project in history
designed to relieve poverty through education.
</P>
<P>
The common goal of ethnic groups throughout China is to achieve
development and social progress. However, the economies in ethnic
regions have lagged behind the eastern coastal areas due to both
historical and natural factors.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, abundant energy, minerals, and land resources in
the central and western areas play a greater role in economic
growth in ethnic regions.
</P>
<P>
Development has opened a new world for people living in ethnic
regions. Members of ethnic groups are now equipped with new ideas
and concepts which have extended their horizons.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous regions are opening wider to the outside world,
with the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region in north China forming
cooperation and trade relations with 82 countries and regions. The
autonomous region has, in fact, introduced some 700 types of goods
to the world market.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic groups in China have established equal, united, and
reciprocal relationships, and will continue to embrace common
prosperity in the future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
