<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Upsurge in Tourism Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- "China Tourism News" reports
that rapid growth of the tourism sector has been accompanied by an
upsurge in educational endeavors.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, some 845 secondary middle schools and
schools of higher education offered at least one department
related to tourism, with a total enrollment of over 204,000 students.
</P>
<P>
In addition, some 150 students across the country were involved
in tourism postgraduate studies.
</P>
<P>
Between 1980-1996, the China National Tourism Administration
sent over 300 students to the United States, Switzerland, Britain,
and Spain to study tourism. The students have returned and
are currenly serving as the backbone of the nation's tourism sector.
</P>
<P>
Tourism education has always stressed on-the-job training, with
a total of 298,849 tourism personnel across the country receiving
various forms of training in 1996 alone.
</P>
<P>
The annual national examination to certify the qualifications
of tourist guides was introduced in 1989, with a second
examination for assigning different levels adopted in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
