<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP-Aided Asset Research Project Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A research project on the
management of state-owned assets, which is aided by the United
Nations Development Program (UNDP), has been officially launched,
the State Administration of State Property (SASP) said here today.
</P>
<P>
The project, which is composed of six sub-projects, is the
first for the SASP to get assistance from the UNDP.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP will supply 700,000 US dollars in technical
assistance. The money will be used to invite overseas experts,
finance overseas inspections, train Chinese professionals in asset
management, and sponsor symposiums.
</P>
<P>
To be implemented by the SASP, the project is of great
significance to deepen reforms in China's state-asset management
system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
