<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean MP Slams Growing Trend of Tribalism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean member of
parliament Lazarus Nzarayebani has warned that tribalism in
Zimbabwe is now a "cancerous disease" which should be wiped out
completely to save the nation from disintegrating.
</P>
<P>
Contributing to debate on the president's speech in
parliament, Nzarayebani said yesterday that tribalism manifested
itself in the governance of the country.
</P>
<P>
He said, "I am not a prophet of doom, but if there is a time
that we have reached doom it is now. It is tribalism that will
make us perish."
</P>
<P>
"We cannot build a nation when we look at ourselves from a
tribal angle. This is dangerous. Zimbabwe must begin to look at
itself as a nation," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said in employing anyone whether in public or private
sector, knowledge and expertise must be the yardstick.
</P>
<P>
He noted, "we must go for knowledge and expertise. If we go
for our tribal sentiments, we are killing Zimbabwe, and all of us
will lose in the process."
</P>
<P>
He stressed, "we must have a national perspective, in
particular us in government. The current situation, the current
behavwill leave Zimbabwe destitute and perpetually a third
world country." 
</P>
</TEXT>
