<HEADLINE> Lesotho Backs Cape Town's Bid for Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho today pledged
its support to South Africa in its bid to bring the Olympic Games
to Africa in 2004.
</P>
<P>
"It is of particular pleasure to wish South Africa well on a
historic occasion like Cape Town bidding to bring the Olympics to
southern Africa and to Africa itself," Lesotho Foreign Minister
Kelebone Maope told reporters in Maseru, the capital of the
land-lock country.
</P>
<P>
Maope congratulated Cape Town, the legislative capital of
South Africa, for attaining a position in the top five countries
competing to host the 2004 games, a report from Maseru said.
</P>
<P>
"However, for us here in Lesotho and in southern Africa, that
is not enough (to be among the top five). We want Cape Town to
come out number one," Maope said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Cape Town, four other well-known cities of
Athens, Rome, Buenos Aires and Stockholm have also bid for the
2004 Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee will announce Friday which
city will host the games. 
