<HEADLINE> Hingis Reaches U.S. Open Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis of
Switzerland stormed into the semifinals of the U.S. Open tennis
championships in New York on Wednesday after defeating doubles
partner Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain, 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, the 16-year-old two-time Grand Slam winner, will meet
American Lindsay Davenport, who fought off Jana Novotna of the
Czech Republic, 6-2, 4-6, 7-6 (7-5) in an afternoon match.
</P>
<P>
Davenport upset Hingis in the semifinals of the Acura Classic
in California earlier this summer.
</P>
<P>
After taking the first set in 28 minutes, Hingis won the first
four games of the second set as Sanchez Vicario, who had trouble
returning Hingis' deep ground strokes, committed 27 unforced
errors, including 15 in the first set.
</P>
<P>
Hingis and Sanchez Vicario, the second-seeded doubles team,
will be on the same side of the court Thursday when they meet
Davenport and Novotna, the third seeds, in a women's semifinal
match.
</P>
<P>
Davenport won a three-set battle with Novotna, taking the
decisive tiebreak to earn a semifinal berth opposite Hingis.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, 21, became the second American to make the
semifinals, joining 17-year-old Venus Williams, who will oppose
Irina Spirlea of Romania. Davenport had a stunning 25 break-point
opportunities and managed to capitalize only six times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
