<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents on Rise in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Traffic accidents have taken at
least 12,000 human lives in Russia so far this year, a National
Traffic Inspection Bureau official said.
</P>
<P>
The official told Russia's Itar-Tass news agency that traffic
violations had doubled since 1992 and among the injured were
13,000 teenagers.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the increase in traffic mishaps mainly to
overspeeding.
</P>
<P>
More than 4.7 million speed violations were reported in the
first half of this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Driving under the influence of alcohol is another cause for
the increase in accidents. This year 830,000 people have been
found driving after drinking, he said.
</P>
<P>
Traffic violations were pervasive even among the staff of the
National Traffic Inspection Bureau, he said. As many as 2,200
staff members have been punished for traffic violations, and among
them 377 have been dismissed and 55 are facing criminal charges.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
