<HEADLINE> Bangladesh PM Leaves for Indonesia, Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina left here this morning on a week-long visit to Indonesia
and the Philippines, at the invitation of President Suharto of
Indonesia and President Fidel Ramos of the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Her 32-member entourage include State Minister for Foreign
Affairs Abdul Hasan Chowdhury, Principal Secretary to the Prime
Minister SA Samad and Foreign Secretary Farooq Sobhan.
</P>
<P>
The visit by the prime minister to the two countries is
basically intended to further firm up the existing "friendly,
fruitful and tangible" relations between Bangladesh and the two
ASEAN countries, sources from the Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Besides holding official talks with Indonesian President
Suharto and Filipino President Ramos, the prime minister will have
talks with business leaders of the two countries. In her meeting
with the business leaders, she will urge them to avail themselves
of the opportunities and the incentives offered by Bangladesh to
investors.
</P>
<P>
The visit in pursuance of the prime minister's declared policy
of "economic diplomacy" is also aimed at further fostering
mutually beneficial trade and economic relations with the two
important countries of the region, a senior official said.
</P>
