<HEADLINE> Turkey, Hungary to Support Each Other in EU Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel said here today that Turkey and Hungary will support each
other in a bid to enter the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
It is the common aim of the two countries to become full-rights
members of the EU, Demirel said at a joint press conference with
his Hungarian counterpart Arpad Goncz.
</P>
<P>
Goncz said that Hungary is expecting assistance from Turkey in
the field of military training.
</P>
<P>
Demirel said his country supports Hungary's bid to join the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) and will help Hungarian
troops prepare to join NATO.
</P>
<P>
Demirel said Turkey is at an important stage in its economic
development, which helps provide a good basis for cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The free trade agreement signed between Turkey and Hungary
early this year may increase the bilateral trade volume to one
billion U.S. Dollars, the Turkish president said.
</P>
<P>
During today's talks, the two presidents also exchanged views
on bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Demirel, who arrived here today, is on a two-day official
visit. 
</P>
