<DOCNO> XIE19970904.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India, France Sign Pact to Boost Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 4 (Xinhua) -- India and France have signed
a bilateral investment promotion and protection agreement in Paris
on Tuesday, the Times of India said today.
</P>
<P>
The accord was penned by Indian Finance Minister P.
Chidambaram, who is on a visit to France, and French Minister of
Economy, Finance and Industry Dominique Strauss-Kahn.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, each government is required to give most
favored nation treatment to investments and investors from the
other country.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will come into force on the date of exchange of
the instruments of ratification.
</P>
<P>
It will remain in effect for a period of 10 years and would
thereafter continue indefinitely unless either government gives
one year's notice of its intention to terminate the agreement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
