<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albania to Get Aid From IMF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary Fund
(IMF) signed an aid agreement here today to help Albania out of
the economic crisis caused by a bogus pyramid-savings scheme early
this year.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached after two weeks of examination of and
negotiation over Albania's economy recovery plan between an IMF
group and the Albanian government.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the IMF will ratify the emergency aid fund
to Albania by the end of October if the recovery plan goes well in
one month, said Juha Kahkonen, head of the IMF group.
</P>
<P>
If this aid plan works well, the IMF may possibly carry out a
three-year-aid program starting from 1998 in Albania, Juha added.
</P>
<P>
However, the IMF imposed a series of conditions on the aid
package, including the privatization of the country's second-class
banks, a cut in budget deficits, an increase of value-added tax,
lowering of inflation rate and reduction of unemployment.
</P>
<P>
Because of the financial crisis early this year, the inflation
rate of Albania has reached 50-60 percent and the budget deficit
accounted for 40 percent of the gross national product.
</P>
<P>
Now 1.2 million people of the 3.2 million population are living
under the poverty line, plus 300,000 unemployed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
