<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguay to Ban Clone of Human Beings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Uruguayan government
will punish people who clone human beings by imposing two to six
years of imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
The bill, elaborated by the National Commission of Cloning and
adopted by the Uruguayan government on Wednesday, will be
submitted to the parliament soon.
</P>
<P>
Cloning human beings would "violate all our fundamental
principles and it is also contrary to the men's condition,"
Minister of Education and Culture Samuel Lichtensztejn said.
</P>
<P>
However, he noted the bill does not mean that the Human
Bioethic Commission can not authorize studies on the generation of
human tissues and research on cancer through clone experiments.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
