<DOCNO> XIE19970904.0260 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oil Weekly Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The following are some of
the most important news stories regarding oil production and trade
gathered from throughout the world over the week.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Brazil will attract foreign funds into its
oil and natural gas industry which will be worth roughly 32
billion U.S. dollars by the year 2002, Brazil's Association of
Infrastructure and Basic Industries reported.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 18.7 billion will go to the state-owned oil
company Petrobras in 101 projects, including a refinery worth 700
million U.S. dollars and the Campos-Victoria gas pipeline worth
150 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
QUITO -- Petroproduccion, a public company Petroecuador's
branch, has increased its oil production to an estimated of
316,000 barrels a day.
</P>
<P>
The manager of Petroproduccion, Bolivar Araujo, said
pre-production trials have enhanced production in several
Amazonian zones, and new fields have been explored with a positive
outcome for the country's oil industry.
</P>
<P>
Abu Dhabi -- Investments from the Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC) countries in petrochemical projects might reach 33 billion
U.S. dollars by 2000.
</P>
<P>
According to a study released by the Doha-based Gulf
Organization for Industrial Consultancy, GCC countries have
developed an up-to-date petrochemical industry to add capital to
their raw oil sales and have also exploited huge reserves of
natural gas.
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- Prices of Venezuelan raw oil ended up with a 0.29
U.S. dollar loss in international markets on August 29, compared
with the price registered a week before, reported the Ministry of
Energy and Mines of Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The institution said the price of a barrel of oil was 15.60
U.S. dollars on Friday as compared to 15.89 dollars the week
before, while the January-August average price reached 16.54
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- Indonesia has discovered natural gas reserves with
a potential volume of 13 billion cubic feet in the eastern region,
Atlantic Richfield Corp. said.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, it said that the new field is located off
Weriagar and Berau archipelagos near Irian Jaya's coast.
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- Net profits from oil exports rose to 9.13 billion
U.S. dollars from January to July, reported the Central Bank of
Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The Bank added oil revenues in the first quarter were worth 1.3
billion U.S. dollars and 1.343 billion U.S. dollars for the second
quarter.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- The Indian government decided to increase oil and
related products prices in an attempt to counter a deficit due to
huge state subvention.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet's decision, which went into effect Monday, involves
an increase of one rupia for a liter of gasoline, up 1.8 rupia for
a liter of diesel and up 15 rupias for a liter of gas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
