<HEADLINE> South Korea to Buy U.S. Military Jets, Missiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- South Korea plans to buy
four Boeing E-767 military radar jets with sophisticated airborne
warning and control system and 248 shoulder-fired "stinger"
anti-aircraft missiles from the United States, the Pentagon said
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The purchase of more than three billion U.S. dollars comes at a
time when the U.S. is urging the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK) to attend the scheduled four-party peace talks on the
Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The Pentagon argued that the purchase is for sea and air
defense of South Korea, where the U.S. deploys 37,000 troops.
</P>
<P>
The sale is expected to be completed without opposition from
Congress, the Pentagon said. 
</P>
