<HEADLINE> Thailand, Laos to Strengthen Economic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials of Laos and
Thailand have agreed in principle to set up a working group on
energy, transport and agriculture in order to deepen bilateral
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached on Wednesday in Champassak, south
Laos, as part of preparations for a ministerial meeting today of
the seventh Lao-Thai Joint Commission, according to a report from
Laos.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is to be co-chaired by the foreign ministers of the
two countries, Somsavat Lengsavad of Laos and Prachuab Chaiyasarn
of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Under the senior officials' agreement, the working group will
discuss details of closer cooperation in the three aspects and
will present its studies to the Joint Commission meeting next
year.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers are expected today to exchange a
document on border crossing, which will make clear how far
Laotians and Thais can travel into each other's countries through
13 border checkpoints along their common border.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, on border demarcation, the two sides have so far
failed to resolve some sticky points and the joint boundary
committee agreed to allow both sides more time to survey and
gather evidence.  
</P>
</TEXT>
