<HEADLINE> Thai Opposition to Lodge No-Confidence Motion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A no-confidence motion will be
filed Monday with Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh as the only
target, opposition leader Chuan Leekpai said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was reached Wednesday at a meeting of leaders of
the five opposition parties.
</P>
<P>
The opposition will hit at the prime minister's failed
management of the country's economic woes and corruption in his
government, opposition sources said.
</P>
<P>
The censure is expected to take place in the last week of this
month, following the Parliament debate on the 1998 fiscal year
budget and a vote on the draft constitution.
</P>
<P>
By political etiquette of the country, if the prime minister
does not receive a vote of confidence, the administration chief
and his cabinet will resign. The prime minister can also choose to
dissolve the house and call snap elections.  
</P>
</TEXT>
