<HEADLINE> Thailand to Issue New Passports for Travelers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Foreign Ministry will
issue a new and thicker passport for the convenience of those
Thais who travel overseas frequently, a senior Thai official said.
</P>
<P>
The new 64-page passport, which will be valid for five years,
would be available beginning on September 8, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Surapong Jayanama said.
</P>
<P>
The current 32-page passport, also valid for five years, will
remain effective and businessmen who regularly tour several
countries will be allowed to have two passports, he was quoted as
saying by local newspapers today.  
</P>
