<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Pakistani English Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are the major
news items in leading Pakistani English newspapers.
</P>
<P>
The News
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Prime Minister Li Peng Wednesday called on China and
Pakistan to open a new era of cooperation that would guide their
relations into the next century.
</P>
<P>
The Nation
</P>
<P>
-- Administrator of the UN Development Program James Gustave
Speth Wednesday advised developing countries to reduce dependence
on donors.
</P>
<P>
The Frontier Post
</P>
<P>
-- The United States' new Assistant Secretary of State for
South Asia, Rick Inderfurth, arrives here today as part of his
five nation tour of the region and will discuss wide-ranging
issues with Pakistani leaders.
</P>
<P>
The Muslim
</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif said Wednesday the government
will effectively implement the national action plan for
maintaining law and order in the country.  
