<HEADLINE> Weapons Ban Imposed in Bogota </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Colombia
prohibits people from carrying any kind of weapons in the capital
between early morning today and October 31, the municipality`s
secretary Alicia Eugenia Silva announced.
</P>
<P>
The official said, during this period only members of regular
state law enforcement institutions could carry authorized
weapons.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken in view of today's rally of about
100,000 workers from all over the country.
</P>
<P>
Silva said, the weapons ban will work to guarantee the
normal development of the upcoming political campaigns in the
Federal District and the local elections scheduled on October
26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
