<HEADLINE> Holyfield to Fight Against Moorer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Evander Holyfield and
Michael Moorer have scheduled their fight on November 8 at New
York's Rockefeller Plaza on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Holyfield, the World Boxing Association (WBA) championship,
considered the rematch as a brand-new challenge, while
International Boxing Federation (IBF) championship Moorer saw it
as a repeat.
</P>
<P>
The 34-year-old Holyfield saw the rematch as a chance for
redemption. "I challenge myself to be the best that I can be. I'm
looking forward to unifying the championships," he said.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Moorer believed that his left-handed style that
bothered Holyfield in their first bout would help him win again.
</P>
<P>
Holyfield will get 20 million U.S. dollars as befits a two-time
conqueror of Mike Tyson, while Moorer will get 8 million
U.S. dollars. The winner could set up a fight with the winner of
the match between Lennox Lewis and Andrew Golota on October 4 at
Atlantic City, New Jersey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
