<HEADLINE> Incendiary Bomb Damages Car in Protest of Olympic Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- An incendiary bomb demolished a
diplomatic car in Athens on Wednesday, whose responsibility was
claimed by a group against the city's bid to host the 2004
Olympics, police said.
</P>
<P>
The car, which belonged to an embassy in Athens, was set ablaze
by gas canisters. No one was hurt.
</P>
<P>
An anonymous caller told Athens radios a group called Struggle
planted to bomb in order to express its opposition to attempts to
stage the Olympics in the city.
</P>
<P>
It was the second attack this week whose aim is to thwart the
Olympic bidding.
</P>
<P>
In similar attack on Monday, the door to the building housing
the headquarters of Greek Olympic Committee was damaged by a bomb.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee will vote on Friday in
Lausanne, Switzerland, on the venue of the 2004 Olympics among
five candidate cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
