<HEADLINE> China's Agricultural Bank Sets up New York Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of
China (ABC), one of the four major commercial banks in the
country, officially declared the opening of its New York
representative office here this evening.
</P>
<P>
Being established in the early 1950s and reestablished in 1979
in Beijing, ABC now maintains 65,870 branches and savings offices
throughout China. It has grown up to be one of the world's biggest
100 banks. The July issue of the London-based magazine, The
Banker, listed ABC as the 47th by assets of 176.779 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shi Jiliang, the bank's president, said at the ceremony that
the representative office of ABC marked a key link in their global
development strategy. It also symbolized a major step forward for
the Chinese bank towards the rank of the world-class banks, he
said.
</P>
<P>
With branches in Singapore and Hong Kong, and representative
offices in London and Tokyo, and now in New York, ABC will
continue to expand and strengthen its overseas presence, Shi said.
</P>
<P>
ABC has so far set up correspondent relations with more than
320 banks around the world. It has also joined both MasterCard
International and Visa International and now issues both Master
Cards and Visa Cards under the name of Golden Spike Card, which
account for more than 25 percent of all cards issued in China.
</P>
<P>
About 300 guests, including senior officials from the Chinese
mission to the United Nations and the Chinese consulate general,
attended the reception. 
</P>
</TEXT>
