<HEADLINE> CPC's 15th Congress Attracting Worldwide Attention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chairman of the Czech Republic and Moravia Communist Party
Miroslav Grebenicek told Xinhua that he wished the meeting a
wholehearted success.
</P>
<P>
"As comrades and friends of the Chinese people, we are watching
the Congress closely because it is a meeting of great
significance."
</P>
<P>
Grebenicek said that China has made "remarkable achievements"
under the leadership of the Chinese Communist Party. It is
well-known that "China is a large country with tremendous
potential and is on the track of rapid development."
</P>
<P>
The Chairman visited China twice in 1992 and 1997 and toured
Beijing, Shanghai and many other Chinese cities. He recalled that
during his stay in China, he saw considerable changes occurring in
both the urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
the Chairman was most impressed by his second visit to China in
February when the Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping passed away. He
said the visit enabled him to witness the profound emotions the
Chinese people expressed for their respected reform architect. He
was also impressed by the determination of the Chinese people to
carry out the policy of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics. 
</P>
