<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Davenport Advances to U.S. Open Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Sixth seed Lindsay
Davenport of the United States advanced to the semifinals of the
U.S. Open tennis championships Wednesday by winning over her
doubles partner Jana Novotna of Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Davenport clinched the victory after she fired a forehand,
cross-court shot to complete the three-set battle resulting 6-2,
4-6, 7-6 (7-5) in her favor.
</P>
<P>
Each player failed to convert a match point in the
tension-filled third set before Davenport finally closed out the
two and a half hour struggle with the third-seeded Czech veteran
to reach her first career Grand Slam semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Davenport became the third player in the final four, joining
17-year-old compatriot Venus Williams and 11th-seeded Romanian
Irina Spirlea.
</P>
<P>
Davenport will take on the winner of Wednesday night's
quarter-final between top seed Martina Hingis and 10th seed
Arantxa Sanchez Vicario, the only player left in the tournament
who has won the Open before.
</P>
<P>
Davenport and Novotna both appeared to take control of the
match in the third set only to lose it. Davenport broke to go up
2-0 and built a 4-1 lead. But Novotna broke back to 4-3, held
serve and then broke again for a 5-4 advantage.
</P>
<P>
Novotna served for a spot in the semifinals, but wasted a match
point and fought off five break points before Davenport broke to
tie the match. They went to the tiebreak and once again both
players surged and faltered. Davenport went up, 3-1, only to have
Novotna rally with three consecutive points for a 4-3 lead.
</P>
<P>
Novotna edged ahead, 5-4, but Davenport stormed back to take
the next three points and close out the match.
</P>
<P>
On the men's side, Greg Rusedski of Britain took on Dutchman
Richard Krajicek in a quarterfinal battle of hard servers.
Fifteenth seed Petr Korda of the Czech Republic, who ousted top
seed and two-time defending champion Pete Sampras of the United
States in a five-set thriller on Monday, had an evening match
against Sweden's Jonas Bjorkman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
