<HEADLINE> Chinese Men Qualify for Team Final at Gymnastics Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese team qualified
for men's final at the World Gymnastics Championships after
ranking the first in the qualifying competition here Wednesday
evening.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, including Huang Xu, Li Xiaopeng, Lu Yufu,
Shen Jian, Xiao Junfeng, and Zhang Jinjing, did well in the six
events of floor, pommel horse, rings, vault, bars, and horizontal
bar.
</P>
<P>
Their total points of 224.394 are 3.427 points more than the
closest rival Russia.
</P>
<P>
Other team qualifiers in the order of ranks are Belarus,
Germany, Japan, and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Chinese gymnasts having qualified for the individual finals are
Huang Xu (all-round), Zhang Jinjing (all-round, pommel horse,
bars), Lu Yufu (all-round), Li Xiaopeng (floor, bars), and Xiao
Junfeng (vault).
</P>
<P>
Qian Kui, one of the leaders of the Chinese delegation, told
Xinhua Wednesday night that both Chinese teams of men and women
would try their best for the team titles on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
