<HEADLINE> Mobile Phone Subscribers Up in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The drop in price and larger
network of mobile phones in Beijing had pushed owners to 470,000
by the end of August, 180,000 more than that at the beginning of
the year.
</P>
<P>
There are 340,000 customers connected with GSM (global system
for mobile communication) network, the remainder are on analogue.
</P>
<P>
The GSM network went into service in Beijing in April, 1995,
covering the whole metropolitan area, including the subways.
</P>
<P>
Roaming services for the GSM network have been established
between Beijing and more than 2,000 cities and counties in 29
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions, as well as Hong
Kong, Macao, Singapore, Finland and Germany.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
