<HEADLINE> IDB Increases Loans to Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) will increase its loans to Brazil, said the
bank's representative to Brazil today.
</P>
<P>
Jorge Elena said the Bank has released 980 million U.S. dollars
in loans from January to August to Brazil, and the whole year's
loan is expected to reach 1.05 billion dollars by December.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the bank granted a loan of 830 million dollars to
Brazil, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
