<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing's Copyright Business Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The copyright business in the
Chinese capital is growing as publishers introduce more books from
overseas.
</P>
<P>
From January to July, more than 60 publishing houses purchased
copyrights to 1,112 books published overseas, an increase of 11
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Social sciences and natural sciences accounted for half, and 80
percent of these came from the United States, Japan and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Top copyright buyers are Electronics Industry Publishing House,
Qinghua University Press, and the Foreign Languages Teaching and
Research Press.
</P>
<P>
Books on computers accounted for 60 percent of the natural
science topics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
