<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Foreign School Co-operation in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A group of students who are
members of the first accounting class run by Chinese Universities
and an Australian will graduate later this month and will receive
a Master's degree recognized in most western and Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
The degree will also be recognized in China after it is
certified by the Academic Degrees Committee of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
This joint project of Guangzhou University, Zhongshan
University, and the University of New South Wales is one of many
Sino-foreign school projects that are on the increase in this
capital of south China's Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
The provincial higher education department has given the
go-ahead to 24 Sino-foreign school projects in the fields of
accounting, foreign languages, computers, international trade,
business administration, and advertising.
</P>
<P>
The foreign partners are Japan, the United States, Canada, and
other countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
