<HEADLINE> Chinese Middle School Students Taught to Say No to Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Middle school students in the
capital of southwest China's Guizhou province are getting an extra
course in a drug education effort this semester, the first of its
kind in China.
</P>
<P>
The course's textbook was compiled by Guiyang's Anti-Drug Office
and Education Committee. It contains information on the harmful
effects of drugs, China's drug laws, and information on how to
fight the drug menace.
</P>
<P>
Southwest China, which borders the Golden Triangle, has been
under a serious threat from criminal activity related to drugs as
overseas drug traffickers open new routes in the area.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
