<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Industrial Output Jumps 3.5 Percent in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Germany's industrial output rose
sharply by 3.5 percent in July from the previous month, the German
Economics Ministry announced today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry today also revised its account of industrial
output growth in June from the previous 1.4 percent to 2.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
Against the same month a year earlier, Germany's industrial
output in July advanced by 5.9 percent after a rise of 3.0 percent
in June.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the stronger-than-expected figures indicated that
the country's economic recovery was well underway.
</P>
<P>
However, there were doubts as to whether the current pace of
growth could be sustained. The Economics Ministry itself also
noted that the latest data may be distorted slightly because this
year's summer holidays fell relatively late, thus reducing the
impact on industrial production in June and July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
