<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberian Election Commission Chief Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Liberia's election
commission Henry Andrews today died of illness at a hospital in the
capital Monrovia.
</P>
<P>
Andrews, in his late 60s, chaired the country's Independent
Elections Commission that organized the July 19 election, which marked
the end of the seven-year civil war with former warlord Charles Taylor
elected the president.
</P>
<P>
According to his daughter, Andrews, who used to be in good health,
told her on Monday that he was not feeling very well. After an medical
examination on Tuesday, "we were told there was a minor heart attack,"
she said, quoted by the British Broadcasting Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The veteran journalist and lawyer told his daughter he was turning
better when she last saw him Tuesday night in the hospital, and was
reported dead this morning.
</P>
<P>
Andrews, who also served as information minister under a previous
Liberian government, was appointed by President Taylor as ambassador
designate awaiting assignment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
