<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Financing to Support Judicial Reform in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of 2 million
U.S. dollars in nonreimbursable financing to Ecuador to help
strengthen its judicial system reform.
</P>
<P>
The financing will support the design and establishment of a
more effective administrative and management system for the
judicial branch, as well as a permanent, decentralized training
and education system to improve judicial career development and
discipline.
</P>
<P>
New technical and legal proposals will be drafted to modernize
the judicial system as well as to improve the services of public
defenders and the ombudsman's office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
